# TASkun Project Overview

TASkun is a Raspberry Pi-based menu system for the TASBot replay device that plays back tool-assisted speedruns on real Famicom/NES hardware.

## Core Components

- **Main Application**: [taskun_r08.py](mdc:taskun_r08.py) - The primary application that handles replay file selection, playback, and user interaction
- **OLED Display**: [oled_display.py](mdc:oled_display.py) - Handles the 1.3" I2C OLED display (SSD1306) for menu navigation and status display
- **Dependencies**: [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt) - Python package dependencies including luma.oled, smbus2, and Pillow
- **Replay Files**: [tasmovies/](mdc:tasmovies/) - Directory containing .r08 replay files for various NES games

## Key Features
- Interactive OLED menu for selecting .r08 replay files
- USB gamepad support for navigation
- Auto-start service for standalone operation
- Visual feedback during playback
- Support for keyboard controls (W/S for navigation, Enter for selection)

## Hardware Requirements
- Raspberry Pi with I2C-enabled OLED display (SSD1306)
- CY8CKIT-059 (PSoC 5LP) flashed with TASBot firmware
- USB gamepad for menu navigation
- NES console and controller port adapter

## Service Management
- [taskun.service](mdc:taskun.service) - Systemd service for auto-start
- [setup_autostart.sh](mdc:setup_autostart.sh) - Setup script for service installation
- [start_taskun_manually.sh](mdc:start_taskun_manually.sh) - Manual startup script
- [stop_taskun_service.sh](mdc:stop_taskun_service.sh) - Service stop script
